nodes.statement_display:
Let $f : A \to \mathbb{R}$ and let $c$ be a cluster point of $A$.
Then $\lim_{x\to c}f(x)=L$ exists for some
$L \in \mathbb{R}$ if and only if
\[
 \ForallOT{\varepsilon},\;
 \ExistsIT{\delta},\;
 \forall x, y \in A :\;
 0<|x-c|<\delta
 \;\wedge\;
 0<|y-c|<\delta
 \;\Rightarrow\;
 |f(x)-f(y)|<\varepsilon.
\]

